<Class name="JSSChangeTrackingInterface" id="38002cd5-2984-46e5-9a11-c97e11a9ccc6">
    <superclass name="JSSChangeTrackingTransient"/>
    <transient/>
    <persistentAllowed/>
    <sharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassPersistentAllowed/>
    <subclassSharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassTransientAllowed/>
    <transientAllowed/>
    <text>This class is the interface to the Change Tracking schema.

It is suggested that you create a reference to this class on
your application class, and then create two applications:

ChangeTracker
ChangeController

then create an initialize method to create this reference (as transient)
and call the appropriate method on this class, i.e.

	create self.myChangeTrackingInterface transient;
	self.myChangeTrackingInterface.initializeController();

then create a finalize method to call the appropriate method on this class
and delete this reference, i.e.

	self.myChangeTrackingInterface.finalizeChangeTracker();
	delete self.myChangeTrackingInterface;


___________________________________________________________________________

